Files in the submission:
        1. lab4b.c: Contains the implemneation of the code. It reads from
        the sensor and stdin at the same time and process the both in paralell
        . Supports the options  --period, --scale and --log from the command
        line. Also it supports
        SCALE=F, SCALE=C, PERIOD=X, OFF, START and STOP while the program is
        running.
        It also suports the digital button input to stop reading
        when wanted by the user.
        2. Makefile: Contains targets and dependecies as required by the
        assignment descriptions.
  default : To build program.
                check : To execute an automated smoke-test of the application
                to see if it runs and can talk to its sensors/actuators.
                clean: It deletes all programs and output generated by the
                Makefile.
                dist : Creates the deliverable tarball
        3. logfile: Contains sample run of output. Although not required but
        still submitting it.
        4. README: File that contain description of all the other files.

